<headline>Winter Weather Advisory issued December 31 at 3:24PM HST until January 01 at 6:00AM HST by NWS Honolulu</headline>
<description>...WINTER WEATHER ADVISORY FOR THE BIG ISLAND SUMMITS TONIGHT...
...WINTER WEATHER ADVISORY IN EFFECT FROM 6 PM THIS EVENING TO
6 AM HST SATURDAY...
* WHAT...Dropping temperatures above 13,000 feet in elevation will
lead to a wintry mix of rain and snow with snow accumulations
of up to one inch.
* WHERE...Big Island Summits.
* WHEN...From 6 PM this evening to 6 AM HST Saturday.
* IMPACTS...Plan on slippery road conditions.</description>
<instruction>A Winter Weather Advisory means that periods of snow, sleet, or
freezing rain will cause travel difficulties. Be prepared for
slippery roads and limited visibilities and use caution while
driving.</instruction>
